---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How to Visit Little Boracay Calatagan Batangas | Travel Guide"
  description="Complete travel guide to Little Boracay in Calatagan, Batangas. How to get there from Manila, what to bring, best time to visit, and everything you need to plan your trip."
>

<script type="application/ld+json" slot="head">{JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HowTo",
  "name": "How to Visit Little Boracay Calatagan Batangas",
  "description": "Step-by-step guide for traveling from Metro Manila to Little Boracay sandbar in Calatagan, Batangas.",
  "totalTime": "PT4H",
  "step": [
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "name": "Drive from Metro Manila to Calatagan, Batangas",
      "text": "Take SLEX South then STAR Tollway toward Batangas. Exit toward Lian then proceed to Calatagan. The drive is approximately 3-4 hours depending on traffic."
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "name": "Reach the coastal jump-off point",
      "text": "Navigate to the coastal barangays of Calatagan where boat operators are based. Several coastal access points exist near local communities."
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "name": "Take the boat to Little Boracay sandbar",
      "text": "Arrange a short boat transfer with local operators to the Little Boracay sandbar. The boat ride is approximately 10-20 minutes depending on water conditions."
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "name": "Enjoy the sandbar and floating cottages",
      "text": "Rent a floating bamboo cottage, swim in the shallow waters, and enjoy the day on the Little Boracay sandbar."
    }
  ]
})}</script>

<!-- Page Header -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="badge badge-ocean">Travel Guide</span>
    <h1>How to Visit Little Boracay</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">Everything you need to plan a perfect trip to the Little Boracay sandbar in Calatagan, Batangas — from Manila drive directions to what to pack.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Quick Summary -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="summary-cards">
      <div class="summary-card">
        <div class="sc-icon">🚗</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Drive Time from Manila</strong>
          <span>3–4 hours via SLEX + STAR Tollway</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="summary-card">
        <div class="sc-icon">🛶</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Boat Transfer</strong>
          <span>Short ride from Calatagan coast (~15–20 min)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="summary-card">
        <div class="sc-icon">☀️</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Best Time to Go</strong>
          <span>Morning to early afternoon, Nov–May</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="summary-card">
        <div class="sc-icon">💰</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Budget</strong>
          <span>Boat fees + cottage rental + meals</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- How to Get There -->
<section class="section" id="how-to-get-there">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>How to Get to Little Boracay from Manila</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Little Boracay is located in <strong>Calatagan, Batangas</strong> — a coastal municipality on the southwestern tip of Batangas Province facing the South China Sea. Here's how to get there:</p>

    <div class="route-steps">
      <div class="route-step">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Drive from Metro Manila</h3>
          <p>Take the <strong>South Luzon Expressway (SLEX)</strong> heading south toward Batangas. Merge onto the <strong>STAR Tollway</strong> and continue south. The total drive from Manila is approximately <strong>3 to 4 hours</strong> under normal traffic conditions. Early morning departures on weekends are recommended to avoid congestion.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="route-step">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Navigate to Calatagan</h3>
          <p>From the STAR Tollway, continue toward <strong>Lian, Batangas</strong> then follow roads toward <strong>Calatagan</strong>. The town center of Calatagan is approximately 15–25 minutes from the coastal jump-off areas used for boat transfers. Navigation apps such as Google Maps or Waze provide up-to-date directions to Calatagan.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="route-step">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Reach the Boat Jump-Off Point</h3>
          <p>From coastal barangays of Calatagan, local boat operators offer transfers to the Little Boracay sandbar. Several access points exist along the coast. It is recommended to contact local operators in advance to confirm availability, especially during peak season and weekends.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="route-step">
        <div class="step-number">4</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Boat Transfer to Little Boracay</h3>
          <p>The boat ride to the Little Boracay sandbar takes approximately <strong>10 to 20 minutes</strong> depending on sea conditions and the specific jump-off point. Boat access may vary depending on weather, tides, and water conditions — always check conditions before heading out.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="nearby-landmarks">
      <h3>Nearby Landmarks for Navigation</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>CaSoBe (Calatagan South Beach)</li>
        <li>Stilts Beach Resort Calatagan</li>
        <li>Calatagan Public Market (town center reference point)</li>
        <li>Club Balai Isabel (nearby Talisay)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Best Time to Visit -->
<section class="section bg-white" id="best-time">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Best Time to Visit Little Boracay</h2>
    <div class="time-grid">
      <div class="time-card time-best">
        <div class="time-header">
          <span>✅ Best Season</span>
          <strong>November – May</strong>
        </div>
        <p>The <strong>dry season</strong> offers the most reliable weather for visiting Little Boracay. Clear skies, calmer seas, and lower tides during morning hours make the sandbar most accessible and beautiful. Peak months are December through April.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="time-card time-caution">
        <div class="time-header">
          <span>⚠️ Typhoon Season</span>
          <strong>June – October</strong>
        </div>
        <p>The wet season brings higher chances of rain, rougher seas, and occasional typhoons. Boat operations may be suspended during bad weather. If visiting during this period, always check weather forecasts and contact local operators first.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="time-card time-tip">
        <div class="time-header">
          <span>⏰ Best Time of Day</span>
          <strong>Morning to Early Afternoon</strong>
        </div>
        <p>Morning visits allow you to see the sandbar at its most visible when tides are lowest. This is also when the light is best for photography. Aim to arrive at the jump-off point by 7–9 AM for the best experience.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- What to Bring -->
<section class="section" id="what-to-bring">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>What to Bring to Little Boracay</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="bring-list card" style="padding: 28px;">
        <h3>✅ Essentials</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Sunscreen (high SPF — reflected water sun is intense)</li>
          <li>Swimwear and extra change of clothes</li>
          <li>Waterproof sandals or aqua shoes</li>
          <li>Dry bag or waterproof pouch for valuables</li>
          <li>Cash (most operators do not accept cards)</li>
          <li>Drinking water and snacks</li>
          <li>Hat and UV-protection rash guard</li>
          <li>Sunglasses (polarized for water glare)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bring-list card" style="padding: 28px;">
        <h3>📸 Optional but Recommended</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Waterproof camera or phone case</li>
          <li>Drone (check regulations first)</li>
          <li>Portable Bluetooth speaker</li>
          <li>Inflatable floaties / pool floats</li>
          <li>Snorkeling mask and fins</li>
          <li>Packed lunch or food to enjoy on the cottage</li>
          <li>First aid kit</li>
          <li>Insect repellent for shore areas</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bring-note">
      <strong>💡 Tip:</strong> Floating cottages typically have limited food service. Bringing your own food and drinks is usually allowed and recommended for a full day trip. Always confirm with your cottage operator.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="section cta-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="cta-inner">
      <h2>Have Questions About Visiting?</h2>
      <p>Join our Facebook community where thousands of visitors share travel tips, photos, and up-to-date information about Little Boracay.</p>
      <div class="cta-actions">
        <a href="https://facebook.com/groups/littleboracay" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Join the FB Community</a>
        <a href="/faq" class="btn btn-outline">Read the FAQ</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.page-hero {
  padding: 60px 0 40px;
  background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--color-ocean-light), var(--color-sand));
}
.page-hero h1 { font-size: 2.6rem; margin: 16px 0 16px; }
.page-lead { font-size: 1.1rem; color: #444; max-width: 640px; }

.summary-cards {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
  gap: 16px;
}
.summary-card {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 14px;
  padding: 20px;
  background: var(--color-white);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}
.sc-icon { font-size: 1.5rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
.summary-card strong { display: block; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.summary-card span { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--color-muted); }

.section-intro { max-width: 700px; color: #444; margin-bottom: 36px; font-size: 1.05rem; }

.route-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; }
.route-step {
  display: flex;
  gap: 24px;
  padding: 28px 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}
.route-step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.step-number {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 44px;
  height: 44px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--color-ocean);
  color: white;
  font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}
.step-content h3 { margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 1.1rem; }
.step-content p { color: #444; font-size: 0.95rem; }

.nearby-landmarks {
  margin-top: 32px;
  padding: 24px;
  background: var(--color-sand-dark);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
}
.nearby-landmarks h3 { margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1rem; }
.nearby-landmarks ul { list-style: disc; padding-left: 20px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
.nearby-landmarks li { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #444; }

.bg-white { background: var(--color-white); }
.time-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; margin-top: 28px; }
.time-card {
  padding: 24px;
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}
.time-best { background: #f0fdf4; border-color: #bbf7d0; }
.time-caution { background: #fffbeb; border-color: #fde68a; }
.time-tip { background: var(--color-ocean-light); border-color: var(--color-sky); }
.time-header { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.time-header span { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--color-muted); }
.time-header strong { font-size: 1rem; }
.time-card p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #444; }

.bring-list h3 { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 1.05rem; }
.bring-list ul { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
.bring-list li { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #444; padding-left: 16px; position: relative; }
.bring-list li::before { content: '•'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--color-ocean); font-weight: 700; }
.bring-note {
  margin-top: 20px;
  padding: 16px 20px;
  background: var(--color-ocean-light);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: #444;
}

.cta-section { background: var(--color-ocean-light); }
.cta-inner {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-ocean-deep), var(--color-ocean));
  border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
  padding: 56px;
  text-align: center;
  color: white;
}
.cta-inner h2 { color: white; font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.cta-inner p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto 28px; }
.cta-actions { display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; }
.cta-inner .btn-primary { background: white; color: var(--color-ocean-deep); }
.cta-inner .btn-outline { border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); color: white; }
.cta-inner .btn-outline:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .summary-cards { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  .time-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .cta-inner { padding: 36px 24px; }
}
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .summary-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .route-step { flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
}
</style>
